Carlson, R. M. K.[Robert M. K.]
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of diamantane, trimantane, tetramantane, and their derivatives in acetone, cyclohexane, ethyl  acetate, toluene, heptane, and 1-pentanol was measured using the solid disappearance method for temperatures  ranging from (273.15 to 348.15) K. The experimental solubility data have been correlated with different  thermodynamic models to obtain engineering parameters for use in process design.
Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Diamantane, Trimantane, Tetramantane, and Their Derivatives in Organic Solvents
